</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4898653A2D7EFFDB4CB84D1DD099F930" pageId="8" pageNumber="211" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="003D36B12D7EFFDB4CB84D1DD099F930" blockId="8.[151,1437,151,1761]" pageId="8" pageNumber="211">
<emphasis id="32F6EAA32D7EFFDB4CB84D1DD07DF948" bold="true" box="[199,328,1663,1689]" pageId="8" pageNumber="211">Etymology</emphasis>
. The new species is named in honour of Prof. Pierfilippo Cerretti, a renowned expert of 
<taxonomicName id="C7824D322D7EFFDB49374D1DD4A9F948" box="[1352,1436,1663,1689]" class="Insecta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="211" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Diptera</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName id="C7824D322D7EFFDB4CE84DC1D024F96C" box="[151,273,1699,1725]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="211" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Tachinidae</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="C7824D322D7EFFDB4D374DC1D0C4F96C" authorityName="Robineau-Desvoidy" authorityYear="1863" box="[328,497,1699,1725]" class="Insecta" family="Rhinophoridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="211" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Rhinophoridae</taxonomicName>
, who was the supervisor of the first author during his Ph.D and spent years working on the Afrotropical flies.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
